Item Name: Short Action Low Capacity Detachable Magazine Assembly
Web Item Name: HS Precision Pro-Series AP300/AP305 Short Action Low Capacity Rifle Magazine .308 Win 4/rd
Web Item Description:
More than simply a convenient way to carry ammunition a quality magazine is an integral part of the function of any precision rifle. H-S Precision magazines whether standard or high capacity provide superior protection for projectiles and flawless feed.

  • .308 Win only

H-S Precision stainless steel conversion kits are designed to convert your Remington 700 BDL hinged floor plate over to a detachable magazine box feeding system. The external dimensions of the floor metal are identical to those of a factory hinged floor plate. Meaning this system will fit any stock with minor to no inletting required. The Pro-Series floor metal is constructed of stainless steel which is teflon coated in a matte black finish. It features two positive lock spring tension levers on the bottom of both sides of the floor metal. These levers create resistance against the polymer coated boot on the bottom of the magazine box to ensure a tight fit and eliminate any rattle whether the box is empty or full. The skeletonized latch located on the front front ot the trigger guard works in conjunction with the robust spring to ensure a positive ejection of the magazine box every time even with gloves on. Each kit comes with installation instructions but for more information of how easy it is to convert your hinged floor plate over to a detachable magazine watch their "Converting to a Detachable Magazine" video.

Item Name: Shield Arms Z9 Pistol Magazine for Glock 43 -  Powercron
Web Item Name: Shield Arms Z9 Handgun Magazine for Glock 43 Black 9mm Luger 9/rd
Web Item Description: When Shield Arms released the S15 magazine for the Glock 43X and 48 they changed the concealed carry game. Using steel instead of plastic for the magazine body allowed them to increase the magazine capacity by 5 rounds without changing the dimensions of the magazine. Now they've applied the same concept to the Glock 43. The Z9 magazine is the same length as the OEM 6-round magazine with the pinky extension but the Z9 hold 9 rounds. That's a 50% increase in capacity with a 0% increase in magazine length! A steel magazine body and durable impact resistant base pad means these mags are built to withstand a lot of abuse. A Powercron coating offers superior resistance to corrosion which is great for anyone who carries their pistol in humid environments or near salt water. These magazines work best when paired with a Shield Arms metal magazine release to avoid wearing down the stock plastic release.

The ProMag AR-15 .223 30-Round Blue Steel Magazine is an exceptional addition to any AR-15 rifle offering both high capacity and outstanding reliability. This magazine stands out for its durable construction designed to withstand the rigors of tactical and recreational use. Its robust steel body treated for heat resistance and finished with a sleek blue oxide ensures long-lasting performance under various conditions.

One of the key features of this ProMag magazine is its 30-round capacity allowing for extended shooting sessions without frequent reloads making it ideal for tactical scenarios target practice or competitive shooting. The magazine's interior boasts a chrome silicon wire spring ensuring consistent feeding and reliability. This spring is designed to maintain tension and function flawlessly over time even with regular use.

The ProMag AR-15 .223 magazine also features a follower that's carefully designed to prevent tilting contributing to its exceptional feeding reliability. This attention to detail in design means that every round is smoothly fed into the chamber reducing the likelihood of jams or misfeeds which is crucial in high-stakes situations.

In addition the magazine’s design allows for easy handling and operation. Its size and shape are optimized for quick and effortless magazine changes while its textured surface provides a secure grip even in wet or slippery conditions. The magazine is also designed to drop free from the firearm when released facilitating quick reloads.

The ProMag AR-15 .223 30-Round Blue Steel Magazine is not only functional but also aesthetically pleasing. Its classic blue steel finish adds a professional and tactical look to any AR-15 setup. It is an ideal choice for shooters who value both aesthetics and performance in their equipment.

  1. Heat-Treated Steel Construction: Ensures durability and resistance to wear.
  2. 30-Round High Capacity: Ideal for extended shooting sessions.
  3. Chrome Silicon Wire Spring: Provides reliable feeding and long-lasting performance.
  4. Anti-Tilt Follower Design: Ensures smooth and consistent ammunition feeding.
  5. Sleek Blue Oxide Finish: Adds a tactical and professional look to the firearm.
  6. MADE IN THE USA

Item Name: MAGPUL PMAG M3 300BLK 30RD BLK
Web Item Name: Magpul MPMAG800BLK PMAG 30 AR 300 B Gen M3 Rifle Magazine Black .300 Blackout 30/rd
Web Item Description:
The PMAG 30 AR 300 B GEN M3 is a purpose-designed magazine for rifles chambered in 300 Blackout. Since its inception 300 Blackout shooters have had to use a magazine designed for another cartridge limiting its ultimate performance and compatibility. One of the nice features of 300 Blackout is the compatibility with 5.56x45mm parts but with the magazine it is a compromise to do so. Due to the wide variety of projectile weights and profiles potentially decreasing overall reliability a dedicated 300 Blackout magazine was a logical step for the PMAG line.

In addition to the performance gained by a dedicated mag the PMAG 30 AR 300 B also offers a safer way to feed your 300 Blackout rifle. When using 5.56x45mm mags the potential to chamber and fire a 300 Blackout round in a 5.56x45mm rifle with catastrophic results requires diligent ammunition management by the shooter. The PMAG 30 AR 300 B’s distinct rib design and smoother upper-half texture provides the shooter a distinct visual and tactile difference from any other PMAG to mitigate dangerous cross-loading issues.
